<body>
<div data-controller="augmentedtriad">
    <h1>Augmented Harmony Player</h1>
<p>
An augmented triad is a three-note chord that consists of a root note, a major third interval above the root, and an augmented fifth interval above the root. In simpler terms, if you start with a note (lets say C), you would add the note four semitones above it (E) and then add the note eight semitones above the original note (G♯). Put them together, and you have a C augmented triad (C-E-G♯).
</p>
<p>
The distinctive feature of an augmented triad is the augmented fifth, which means the fifth is raised by one semitone compared to a perfect fifth. This creates a unique and somewhat "tense" sound. Augmented triads are less common than major and minor triads but are used in various musical contexts for their specific tonal color.

In summary, an augmented triad consists of a root note, a major third, and an augmented fifth, giving it a bright and somewhat dissonant quality.
</p>
    <!-- Dropdown for selecting harmonies -->
    <label for="harmonySelect">Select Harmony:</label>
    <select id="harmonySelect">
        <option value="0">C Augmented</option>
        <option value="1">F Augmented</option>
        <option value="2">G Augmented</option>
        <option value="3">A Augmented</option>
        <option value="4">D Augmented</option>
        <option value="5">E Augmented</option>
        <option value="6">B Augmented</option>
        <option value="7">Db Augmented</option>
        <option value="8">Eb Augmented</option>
        <option value="9">Ab Augmented</option>
        <option value="10">Bb Augmented</option>
    </select>

    <!-- Buttons for notes -->
    <div id="noteButtons">
        <!-- Note buttons will be dynamically added here -->
    </div>

    <button id="playButton">Play Harmony</button>
    <button id="stopButton">Stop</button>
</body>
